HEADWORD: Sideboard
<hw>Side"board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A piece of
dining-room furniture having compartments and shelves for keeping or
displaying articles of table service.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>At a stately <qex>sideboard</qex>, by the wine,⟦br⟧
That fragrant smell diffused.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sidebone</ent>⟦br⟧
